item.title: Wanting is easy - Doing has just become harder
item.author: Alexander Deprez
item.description: Knowing what I want is quite easy at this point in my life: To be a awesome father to my daughter. To be a great husband to my wife. To be healthy and fit. Defining what this means for me and comming up with a plan to achieve this is still in the realm of doable. What I find hard, and you can call me a winey baby, is the actual doing.
